import numpy as np
import math

def boxcar_matched_filter(profile, width):
    result = np.zeros(len(profile))
    sqrt_width = math.sqrt(width)
    
    for i in range(len(profile)):
        sum_val = 0
        for j in range(width):
            sum_val += profile[(i+j) % len(profile)]
        result[i] = sum_val / sqrt_width
    
    return result
